Engaged in Our Community

The Woodinville Garden Club extends our interest in gardening, horticultural education, civic beautification and environmental stewardship through various civic projects. These projects allow us to make a difference in our community, the region and the world.

Our annual plant sale and garden tour events raise funds to support club operations and our ongoing and future civic projects. Our Reserve Fund Committee actively researches prospective projects for our club to support.

Our most recent civic engagement was the donation of $15,000 toward the development of the new Visitor & Education Centers at the Bellevue Botanical Gardens.


Some of our past projects have included those pictured here:


Georgia Gerber $25,000 bronze sculpture for Woodinville Playing Fields.

Jerry Wilmot Gateway Park $20,000 funding.

"The Gardener" bronze statue by Georgia Gerber at DeYoung Park.

Northshore Adult Day Center raised bed plantings.

Seattle Children's Play Garden chicken coop and rabbit hutch.


To learn more about the WGC's history of civic involvement, go to Civic Project Listing.

Welcome to The Maker Station!
-- Marietta's Makerspace --

The Maker Station Inc is home to a vibrant community of local makers in Cobb County and the greater Atlanta metro area. Here curious and like-minded folks come together to work on projects, discover new areas of interest, develop a new business idea, or simply grow their personal hobbies. The makerspace is a 100% volunteer driven 501c3 non-profit corporation. We are a valuable resource for Smyrna, Marietta, Kennesaw, Acworth, and surrounding metro areas. We started our journey in 2014 to build a makerspace close to home and welcome all interested community members to help grow and shape this makerspace / hackerspace into a thriving, collaborative environment.

How to Join

Joining is easy! Just follow these steps and you will be on your way in no time.

  1. Visit the join page to select the type of membership that applies to you
  2. Click through and complete your transaction to set up recurring billing.
  3. Join the Meetup group to keep track of our events
  4. Join the Slack messenger group by sending an email to and asking for Slack access.
  5. Read through the information on our Policies and Procedures page
  6. Go Make something!

History of the Club



The Shetland Sheepdog Club of Wales was inaugurated with the Kennel Club in 1969.  To start off we held 2 Open Shows and 1 Limit Show a year held in conjunction with the Rough and Smooth Collies. This continued until we were granted Championship status in 1974.


Our first Championship Show was held in October at Sophia Garden Pavilion in Cardiff, the judge being Mrs M Guest.  Our Championship Show moved to Pontypool Leisure Centre in October 1975, and changed its date to March. This venue was popular and we remained there until 2004 when, due to refurbishments, we had to move and all our shows were then held at the Sports Stadium at Cwmbran. However, due to refurbishments at the Stadium, we had the opportunity to once more return to Pontypool which is now the current home for the Club’s Championship Show.  Open shows are held at the Beaufort Centre in Newport.


Our Open Shows are held in January and September, and our Championship Show in March.  The judges for our Championship show are chosen by a ballot of the membership.


The club holds a judging list and anyone wishing to apply can contact the Secretary.  All applications are considered by a judges sub committee.  The secretary holds details of the latest Judges List (and criteria) and can provide this on request.


We also put on social events for our members – all welcome.   A newsletter, ‘Newsflash’, is also produced at the end of each year and sent to all members.  If anyone else would like a copy please contact the Secretary.


The officers and committee are always happy to help with any enquires.   For details of committee click on Committee
